# Observable output-sensitivity fixture (GH #197).
#
# Linear mass-action chain  A --k1--> B --k2--> C  (all elementary, so the
# codegen sensitivity RHS engages and the IC axis is available). The groups
# exercise the observable chain rule d obs/dθ = Σ_i c_ji·dx_i/dθ:
#   - A_obs      = A           single species, unit coefficient
#   - BC2        = B + 2*C     multi-species, NON-unit coefficient, time-varying
#   - Total      = A + B + C   conserved (=100): d/dp ≈ 0, d/dA(0) ≈ 1
begin parameters
    1 k1 0.30
    2 k2 0.15
end parameters
begin species
    1 A() 100
    2 B() 0
    3 C() 0
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 2 k1 #A_to_B
    2 2 3 k2 #B_to_C
end reactions
begin groups
    1 A_obs 1
    2 BC2   2,2*3
    3 Total 1,2,3
end groups
